Durban - Two police officers have appeared briefly in the Durban Specialised Commercial Crime court on charges of corruption. The officers, Sergeant Msawenkosi Mabaso and Sergeant Thulani Dlangalala, both aged 45, are based at the Berea police station. They were arrested on May 9.

According to the Directorate for Priority Crime Investigation also known as the Hawks, the officers allegedly offered to release a man, charged for reckless and negligent driving. AdChoicesADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads

Hawks spokesperson in KwaZuu-Natal, Captain Simphiwe Mhlongo, said the man was arrested near the King Shaka International Airport in 2016. The officers allegedly told the man they would release him in exchange for a bribe. 

"The Hawks were alerted and an undercover operation was conducted, resulting in the arrest and recovery of money taken from the complainant. They have each been granted R2000 bail. The case has been postponed to May 21 pending further investigation," he said. 
